
.TH "GCLOUD_BETA_COMPUTE_RESERVATIONS_SET\-IAM\-POLICY" 1



.SH "NAME"
.HP
gcloud beta compute reservations set\-iam\-policy \- set the IAM policy for a Compute Engine reservation



.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP
\f5gcloud beta compute reservations set\-iam\-policy\fR (\fIRESERVATION\fR\ :\ \fB\-\-zone\fR=\fIZONE\fR) \fIPOLICY_FILE\fR [\fIGCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG\ ...\fR]



.SH "DESCRIPTION"

\fB(BETA)\fR Set the IAM policy for the given reservation as defined in a JSON
or YAML file.



.SH "POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS"

.RS 2m
.TP 2m

Reservation resource \- The reservation to set the IAM policy for. The arguments
in this group can be used to specify the attributes of this resource. (NOTE)
Some attributes are not given arguments in this group but can be set in other
ways. To set the [project] attribute: provide the argument [reservation] on the
command line with a fully specified name; set the property [core/project];
provide the argument [\-\-project] on the command line. This must be specified.

.RS 2m
.TP 2m
\fIRESERVATION\fR
ID of the reservation or fully qualified identifier for the reservation. This
positional must be specified if any of the other arguments in this group are
specified.

.TP 2m
\fB\-\-zone\fR=\fIZONE\fR
The name of the Google Compute Engine zone.

.RE
.sp
.TP 2m
\fIPOLICY_FILE\fR
Path to a local JSON or YAML formatted file containing a valid policy.

The output of the \f5get\-iam\-policy\fR command is a valid file, as is any JSON
or YAML file conforming to the structure of a Policy
(https://cloud.google.com/iam/reference/rest/v1/Policy).


.RE
.sp

